  "texts": [
    "Finally, the last central stage of ML-based tools is to decide when to stop the screening process.",
    "Active learning methods use an iterative feedback loop in which the algorithm learns from the decisions made by the human reviewer and integrates this information to predict the next document with the highest probability of inclusion.",
    "However, the final decision regarding the inclusion or exclusion of a study and when to stop screening rests with the researcher.",
    "After a reviewer decides to include or exclude a study, the algorithm incorporates this information to update its training and predict the next study deemed most relevant for review.",
    "This process continues until the reviewer decides to stop the review process or all the studies in the literature database are classified."
  ],
